    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of the species Chloroxylon swietenia, native to southeast Asia, India, and Sri Lanka. It is a silky, golden-colored wood used for fine cabinetwork, veneer, and farming tools.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
